The ONNX backend compiles, but its runtime fallback logic does not catch a common ORT execution-provider registration failure path, allowing silent CPU fallback when a GPU provider was requested. This violates the new loud-fallback/device-selection contract.

Review comment:

- [P2] Force ORT provider registration failures to surface — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-10-20260708T192441Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder/src/ort_bge.rs:329-329
  When a non-CPU provider is reported available but cannot actually register at session creation time (for example, CUDA/ROCm support is compiled into ORT but the host is missing CUDA/cuDNN/ROCm runtime libraries or the device id is bad), `ExecutionProviderDispatch` defaults to `fail_silently`, so `with_execution_providers` returns `Ok` after logging internally and falling back to CPU. That means `build_session_with_fallback` never receives an `Err`, `build_warn` stays `None`, and this path can still run on CPU silently despite the intended loud fallback; use `error_on_failure()` for the attempted non-CPU provider so the retry/warning logic actually executes.
